'''8406集团'''（{{lang-vi|Khối 8406}}）是一个由[[越南|越南]][[天主教|天主教]]人士领导政治联盟团体，谋求[[越南民主运动|越南民主化]]改革。2006年8月4日，多位越南的民运人士发表《2006年越南自由民主宣言》（Tuyên Ngôn Tự Do Dân Chủ Cho Việt Nam 2006），宣称越南必须进行民主改革，此宣言在同年的4月8日被118位[[异见人士|异见人士]]签署，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.upi.com/Emerging_Threats/2009/10/09/Vietnam-clamps-down-on-democracy-activists/UPI-48301255093200/ |title=Vietnam clamps down on democracy activists |date=9 October 2009 |publisher=United Press International |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2015-12-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222101901/http://www.upi.com/Emerging_Threats/2009/10/09/Vietnam-clamps-down-on-democracy-activists/UPI-48301255093200/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>后来这个组织被称为“8406集团”，支持者人数增长到数万人。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.atimes.com/atimes/Southeast_Asia/HI14Ae01.html |title=Heed the call of Vietnam's Bloc 8406 |author=Shawn W. Crispin |date=14 September 2006 |work=Asia Times Online |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2017-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170626052543/http://www.atimes.com/atimes/Southeast_Asia/HI14Ae01.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==著名的集团成员==
天主教神父[[阮文理_(人權活動家)|阮文理]]在2007年3月30日因为支持该组织的宣言，被判处8年有期徒刑。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.asianews.it/index.php?l=en&art=8872&size= |title=Catholic Priest, Fr. Nguyen Van Ly, condemned to 8 years in prison |author=Nguyen Van Tranh |date=30 March 2007 |work=Asia News |accessdate=21 July 2012 |archive-date=2019-02-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190215083536/http://www.asianews.it/index.php?l=en&art=8872&size= |dead-url=no }}</ref>他在2011年被释放，但同年又被关回监狱。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hrw.org/news/2011/07/26/vietnam-father-nguyen-van-ly-should-remain-free |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2015-08-21 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924144514/http://www.hrw.org/news/2011/07/26/vietnam-father-nguyen-van-ly-should-remain-free |dead-url=no }}</ref>

律师、劳工活动家{{link-en|陈国贤|Trần Quốc Hiền}}被指控为8406集团成员。2007年他受审，被以危害国家安全罪判处五年有期徒刑。<ref name=HRW>{{cite book |title=Not yet a workers' paradise: Vietnam's suppression of the independent workers' movement |last=Human Rights Watch |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |year=2009 |publisher=Human Rights Watch |location= |isbn= |page=24 |pages= |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=VgAO5tpkWeoC&pg=PA24&lpg=PA24&dq=Tran+Quoc+Hien&source=bl&ots=vLPeZbON4c&sig=mrZoOcgQU0LHrhhjNNGTC5cyCik&hl=en&sa=X&ei=lSwWT_f4HMeqgwfJ3bn4Aw&ved=0CCgQ6AEwADgK#v=onepage&q=Tran%20Quoc%20Hien&f=false |accessdate=18 January 2012}}</ref>他也在网络上发表批评政府的文章，例如“追踪”（The Tail），描述被政府管制下的生活。<ref name=HRW />

前[[越共|越共]]官员{{link-en|韦德回|Vi Đức Hồi}}加入了这个集团，后来在2007年退出。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.amnesty.org/en/news-and-updates/viet-nam-activist-prison-sentence-condemned-2011-01-26 |title=Viet Nam activist prison sentence condemned |date=26 April 2011 |publisher=Amnesty International |accessdate=20 July 2012 |archive-date=2014-12-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141207204112/http://www.amnesty.org/en/news-and-updates/viet-nam-activist-prison-sentence-condemned-2011-01-26 |dead-url=no }}</ref>2011年，他转发亲民主的文章后，被当局以“传播反政府言论罪”监禁。<ref name=FN>{{cite web |url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2011/01/26/vietnamese-dissident-sentenced-years-jail/ |title=Vietnamese dissident sentenced to 8 years in jail |date=26 January 2011 |publisher=Fox News |agency=Associated Press |accessdate=20 July 2012 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924180713/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2011/01/26/vietnamese-dissident-sentenced-years-jail/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>
